<div id="review_819529827" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/819529827" />
    <a title="Velma" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1843025-velma"><img alt="Velma" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611872131p2/1843025.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/819529827?book_show_action=true">Jan 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Velma" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Velma" href="/user/show/1843025-velma">Velma</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780020160908" href="/book/show/384582.Helliconia_Spring">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1843025-velma?shelf=2021-reads">2021-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1843025-velma?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1843025-velma?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1843025-velma?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer819529827" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12806262942372095526">Combining elements of both science fiction and fantasy, Brian Aldiss’ Helliconia trilogy is an epic spanning thousands of years across multiple planets. A masterpiece of world building, its strength lies in the breadth of disciplines from which Aldiss draws. History, anthropology, biology, climate science, astronomy, and political science all undergird three stand-alone stories that are linked by a Gaia-inspired environmental thesis in an attempt to ask questions about religion, spirituality, su</span>
  <span id="freeText12806262942372095526" style="display:none">Combining elements of both science fiction and fantasy, Brian Aldiss’ Helliconia trilogy is an epic spanning thousands of years across multiple planets. A masterpiece of world building, its strength lies in the breadth of disciplines from which Aldiss draws. History, anthropology, biology, climate science, astronomy, and political science all undergird three stand-alone stories that are linked by a Gaia-inspired environmental thesis in an attempt to ask questions about religion, spirituality, survival, community, and government.<br /><br />Helliconia Spring, the first volume, took me a long time to get into, but I’m glad I stuck with it. The ending hooked me. The middle installment, Helliconia Summer, is my favorite; it has the best character development, IMO. Finally, Helliconia Winter was a little ambitious and went a little off the rails in places, but wrapped up the trilogy in a satisfying way. <br /><br />Note: suffice it to say it’s a damn weird coincidence that my first read of the year, Helliconia Spring, is about an RNA virus that ravages a planet. I did NOT have that in my 2021 bingo card.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12806262942372095526" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


