<span id="freeTextContainer11238941052310681317">Pseudonyms: <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6981687.Jael_Cracken' title='Jael Cracken' rel='nofollow noopener'>Jael Cracken</a>, Peter Pica, John Runciman, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5245615.C_C__Shackleton' title='C.C. Shackleton' rel='nofollow noopener'>C.C. Shackleton</a>, Arch Mendicant, &amp; &quot;Doc&quot; Peristyle.<br/><br/>Brian Wilson Aldiss was one of the most important voices in science fiction writing today. He wrote his first novel while working as a bookseller in Oxford. Shortly afterwards he wrote his first work of science fiction and soon gained international recognition. Adored for his innovative literary</span>
  <span id="freeText11238941052310681317" style="display:none">Pseudonyms: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/6981687.Jael_Cracken" title="Jael Cracken" rel="nofollow noopener">Jael Cracken</a>, Peter Pica, John Runciman, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5245615.C_C__Shackleton" title="C.C. Shackleton" rel="nofollow noopener">C.C. Shackleton</a>, Arch Mendicant, &amp; "Doc" Peristyle.<br /><br />Brian Wilson Aldiss was one of the most important voices in science fiction writing today. He wrote his first novel while working as a bookseller in Oxford. Shortly afterwards he wrote his first work of science fiction and soon gained international recognition. Adored for his innovative literary techniques, evocative plots and irresistible characters, he became a Grand Master of Science Fiction in 1999.<br /> Brian Aldiss died on August 19, 2017, just after celebrating his 92nd birthday with his family and closest friends.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/group/show/23049.Brian_W_Aldiss_Appreciation_Group" rel="nofollow noopener">Brian W. Aldiss Group on Good Reads</a></span>
